@page
@model PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Project Notes";
}

<section class="panel note-panel">
    <div class="summary-head">
        <h1>Project Notes</h1>
        <span>Architecture, scope, and roadmap</span>
    </div>

    <div class="notes-grid">
        <article class="note-card">
            <h2>Why This Exists</h2>
            <p>
                Route Analyzer turns a one-off <code>ping</code> plus <code>tracert</code> run into a readable path report.
                The goal is to make first-pass network troubleshooting easier than scanning raw terminal output.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="note-card">
            <h2>Infra / SRE Angle</h2>
            <p>
                The app is intentionally shaped like an incident triage tool: structured summaries, exportable evidence,
                runtime metadata, health checks, and configuration validation are part of the product, not afterthoughts.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="note-card">
            <h2>How It Works</h2>
            <p>
                The shared diagnostics engine runs native ICMP probes, executes platform traceroute commands,
                enriches public hops with PTR and geo data, then scores the path as <em>Stable</em>, <em>Observe</em>, <em>Investigate</em>, or <em>Critical</em>.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="note-card">
            <h2>Tooling Modes</h2>
            <p>
                This project is now delivered as Web UI + Web API + CLI executable, so diagnostics can be run locally on affected machines
                and still be consumed in dashboards or automation pipelines.
            </p>
        </article>

        <article class="note-card">
            <h2>Current Limits</h2>
            <p>
                Traceroute command availability depends on host environment. Geo enrichment depends on <code>ipwho.is</code>,
                and the tool is designed for single-run diagnostics, not long-term telemetry collection.
            </p>
        </article>
    </div>
</section>
